title.rendered: Barbados vs Jamaica, Final, Caribbean T20 League: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score:190

2nd innings average score: 137

Type: Good batting wicket.

Time: October 1, 4.30 AM IST

Teams

Probable XI for Barbados: Rahkeem Cornwall, Kyle Mayers (c), Harry Tector, Azam Khan, Najibullah Zadran, Jason Holder, Devon Thomas (wk), Mujeeb Ur Rahman, Obed McCoy, Hayden Walsh, Ramon Simmonds

Probable XI for Jamaica: Brandon King, Kennar Lewis (wk), Shamarh Brooks, Rovman Powell (c), Raymon Reifer, Fabian Allen, Mohammad Nabi, Imad Wasim, Chris Green, Nicholson Gordon, Mohammad Amir

Form Concern

It has been a struggle for Najibullah Zadran with the bat lately. His recent scores in the format read 2, 0, 0, 10, and 17.

Game Changers

A 15-ball 41 cameo by Imad Wasim was instrumental in pushing Jamaica’s total over 225. Later, he also got a two-for to make it to the Ultimate Team.

Through his consistent six-hitting, Azam Khan has provided 15 bonus points. He has registered 2 half-centuries in the run-up to the finals.

Smart Picks

A 52-ball 109 (7 fours and 8 sixes) by Shamarh Brooks against Guyana not only helped Jamaica qualify for the finals but also saw him generate maximum points (80) on My11Circle.

Chris Green did leak 40 runs in 4 overs but was successful in dismissing Shai Hope and Shakib Al Hasan in quick succession, thereby adding vital 20 points.

Going into the all-important final, Mujeeb Ur Rahman has picked 10 wickets in 6 games. He has already added on multiple occasions for maintaining an economy of 5.13 RPO.

Jason Holder is the second-highest wicket-taker (16) in this edition. He earlier took 5 wickets in 2 outings against Jamaica, earlier in the tournament.

Power Players

By the virtue of being the leading wicket-taker (18) in the tournament, Mohammad Amir has made it to the Ultimate Team several times. A repeat in the finals cannot be ruled out.

Be it with the bat or ball, Kyle Mayers hasn’t disappointed fantasy players. Besides adding 337 runs at 31, including the highest score of 79, he has bagged 7 wickets.

Fantasy Tips of The Day

– Barbados have plenty of firepower in the batting, across positions. As a matter of fact, they have hit the most sixes (87) for the tournament.

– Very rarely does Rakheem Cornwall stay beyond the powerplay. He doesn’t prefer running between the wickets.
